Abominable Workflows v3
=======================
https://civitai.com/models/420163/abominable-workflows

REQUIRED FILES
--------------
 To use these workflows, you need to install the following models in ComfyUI.
 Place them in the specified directories:

 <your_comfyui_dir> / models / checkpoints /
   > pixart_sigma-FP16.safetensors
   > photon_refiner-FP16.safetensors

 <your_comfyui_dir> / models / clip /
   > t5_xxl_encoder-FP8.safetensors

 <your_comfyui_dir> / models / vae /
   > pixart_vae.safetensors

 All four files can be downloaded from:
   https://huggingface.co/martin-rizzo/AbominableWorkflows/tree/main

REQUIRED NODES
--------------
 Abominable workflows also requires the following custom nodes:

   > ComfyUI_ExtraModels
     https://github.com/city96/ComfyUI_ExtraModels

   > ComfyUI-Crystools
     https://github.com/crystian/ComfyUI-Crystools

 For detailed installation instructions for these nodes, please refer to the main page of Abominable Workflows.

OUTPUT IMAGES
-------------
 Generated images will be automatically saved in:
    <your_comfyui_dir> / output / abominable /

WORKFLOWS INCLUDED
------------------
 This pack contains multiple workflows, each designed for a different image style:
   > abominable_1GIRL_
   > abominable_DARKFAN80_
   > abominable_INK_
   > abominable_MILO_
   > abominable_PHOTO_
   > abominable_PIXEL_
  
IMAGE SIZE
----------
 Abominable uses PixArt-1024 beyond its recommended size.
 For optimal quality, consider using the values provided by PixArt's authors:

    9:21 =  640 x 1536
    9:16 =  768 x 1344
    4:5  =  896 x 1152
    2:3  =  832 x 1216
    1:1  = 1024 x 1024
    3:2  = 1216 x  832
    5:4  =  896 x 1152
   21:9  = 1536 x  640
   16:9  = 1344 x  768

A tiny hedgehog wrapped snugly in a miniature blanket, holding a small cup of hot chocolate with both paws, sitting on a wooden floor. Near a fireplace made of stacked shiny stones

* Seed              : random
 * Guidance          : 3.2     [ 3.0 - 4.0 ]
 * Refiner intensity : 22      [ 18  - 25  ]
 * Refiner variation : 0       < different values create slight changes in small details
 * Refiner attention : empty   < add words to focus refinement on specific objects
 * Ref.ignores prompt: false   < if enabled, the refiner will completely ignore the prompt

If the image looks too drawn, add "bokeh" or "macrophoto" to the prompt.
If the background is blurry, add one or more of the following to the negative prompt:
    bokeh, out of focus, macrophoto
Enabling 'HQ sampler' can improve contrast and details, but slower and doesn’t always help.

For more information about Abominable Workflows:
https://civitai.com/models/420163
